This step involves creating a [Widget Blueprint](Engine/UMG/UserGuide/WidgetBlueprints) which will be used to draw the HUD on screen. 

1. With project open, inside the **Game** folder of the **Content Browser**, click the **New** button and select **New Folder** and call it **UMG**. 

1. Open the **UMG** folder, then **Right-click** and select **User Interface** then **Widget Blueprint** and name it **GameHUD**.  

		![](New_3.png)

		No matter what type of HUD elements you wish to create in **UMG**, you will always first need to create a **Widget Blueprint**. 

In the next section, we will begin adding elements to the **Widget Blueprint** that we want to display on screen. 

